comments:
I really had trouble answering these questions because there is so much we don't know. They're aliens after all and their social conditions/constraints or the society they live in could be totally different from the ones that we know. 
However, there is only one question that really deals with finding out how the participants "perceive happiness in others". And that is the first one where you ask if the alien is happy. You basically already give us the answer: all of them are happy with their life and with what they are doing. So, by knowing that, we can only agree. Because that's all we know. 
The other two questions are on one side difficult and on the other side they're very simple. In my opinion, I can't judge the life of other people (or aliens). If they had the feeling that their life was good, if they didn't experience sadness or lonliness or other bad feelings, then they lived a good life... no matter what the results of this life are. Even if their life results in bad conditions for others they still lived a good and fulfilling life. The fact that the outcome of their life makes the life of other people worse doesn't change the quality of their own life. 
In my eyes, only the person/alien living the life can answer the question of whether this life is good or bad.
